  "tool_calls": [
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 debug read-peripheral RCC",
        "description": "Read RCC peripheral registers to check USART2 clock enable bit"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "grep -i \"usart2\" /home/user/.claude/projects/-home-user-claude-projects-stm32-substrate-tests-fixtures-projects-STM32CubeL4-Projects-NUCLEO-L476RG-Examples-GPIO-GPIO-IOToggle-STM32CubeIDE/2af62a5e-8b0f-473c-b603-4ab9b66edc8b/tool-results/bmry902tc.txt",
        "description": "Search RCC output for USART2 clock enable field"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "python3 -c \"\nimport json, re\nwith open('/home/user/.claude/projects/-home-user-claude-projects-stm32-substrate-tests-fixtures-projects-STM32CubeL4-Projects-NUCLEO-L476RG-Examples-GPIO-GPIO-IOToggle-STM32CubeIDE/2af62a5e-8b0f-473c-b603-4ab9b66edc8b/tool-results/bmry902tc.txt') as f:\n    data = json.load(f)\n\nregs = data['registers']\n# APB1ENR1 holds USART2EN on L476\nfor reg_name in ['APB1ENR1', 'APB1ENR', 'APB1LENR']:\n    if reg_name in regs:\n        reg = regs[reg_name]\n        print(f'Register: {reg_name}  raw=0x{reg[\\\"raw_value\\\"]:08X}')\n        for fname, fval in reg['fields'].items():\n            if 'USART2' in fname.upper() or 'UART2' in fname.upper():\n                print(f'  {fname}: raw_value={fval[\\\"raw_value\\\"]}  (bit {fval[\\\"bit_offset\\\"]})')\n        break\nelse:\n    print('APB1ENR1/APB1ENR not found. Available registers:')\n    print([k for k in regs if 'APB' in k or 'ENR' in k])\n\"\n",
        "description": "Parse RCC JSON to extract USART2EN from APB1ENR1"
      }
    }
  ],
  "final_text": "**Yes \u2014 the RCC enable bit was forgotten. USART2 clock is OFF.**\n\nHere's what the hardware says:\n\n| Register | Field | Bit | Value |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `RCC->APB1ENR1` | `USART2EN` | 17 | **0 (disabled)** |\n\nThe entire `APB1ENR1` register reads `0x00000000`, meaning no APB1 peripheral clocks are enabled at all \u2014 not just USART2.\n\n**Fix:** you need to set bit 17 of `RCC->APB1ENR1` before touching any USART2 register. In CMSIS/HAL terms:\n\n```c\n// Bare-metal\nRCC->APB1ENR1 |= RCC_APB1ENR1_USART2EN;\n\n// HAL macro equivalent\n__HAL_RCC_USART2_CLK_ENABLE();\n```\n\nThis must happen **before** any write to `USART2->BRR`, `USART2->CR1`, etc. \u2014 reads/writes to a clock-gated peripheral return unpredictable values (bus returns 0 or a fault depending on the core's error response configuration)."
}